Who or which of many;
{#api jYAyate katamena digBAgena gataH sa#} 
{#jAlma iti#} <ls>V. 1</ls>; {#aTa katamaM#} 
{#punarftumaDikftya gAsyAmi#} <ls>Ś. 1</ls>; {#katame te guRAstatraM#}
{#yAnudAharaMtyAryamiSrAH#} <ls>Māl. 1</ls>; <ls>G. L. 22</ls>;
(sometimes it is used merely as a
strengthened substitute for {#kim#}).
When followed by {#ca#} and preceded
by {#yatama#} it means ‘any whosoever’,
‘whatsoever’. In negative sentences
{#katama#} with {#cana#} or {#api#} means ‘not
even one’, ‘none at all’ It also means
‘best or excessively good-looking’.
